      "id": "piyo_yuramon",
      "displayName": "Yuramon",
      "stage": "Baby I",
      "line": "piyomon",
      "spriteFile": "Yuramon",
      "comment": "NOT a duplicate of the `yuramon` node in the palmon line — it is the same Digimon in a second tree. The V4 tree roots both Piyomon and Palmon at Fresh: Yuramon -> In-Training: Tanemon, and both ids were already taken by the palmon line (US-008). US-045 gave this line its own ids rather than sharing the existing nodes, because `line` is single-valued and the Dex draws one tree per line: a shared node can sit in only one tree, which would leave piyo_digitama's edge pointing outside its own tree and EvolutionTreeLayout would silently drop the connector. Same art, same displayName, distinct id — which is exactly what the id/spriteFile split in docs/evolutions-schema.md is for.",
